               <history>
                 <origin>
                    <origDate notBefore="1897" notAfter="1971">Possibly 1897-1971.</origDate>
                   <ref type="mss" corresp="DSEthiop20">DS Ethiop. 20</ref> and <ref type="mss" corresp="DSEthiop17">DS Ethiop. 17</ref> belong together; they are
                   probably a part of an unfinished manuscript started in
                   <placeName ref="LOC2804Egypt">Egypt</placeName>.
               The text mentions <foreign xml:lang="gez">ʾabuna Lǝqwas (Luqās?)</foreign>,
               <locus target="#1v"/>, who is difficult to identify. ʾAbbā Qerǝllos, mentioned as <foreign xml:lang="gez">
               አባ፡ ቄርሎስ፡ ዘሀገር፡ አባይ፡ እለ፡ እስክንድርያ፡</foreign> in <locus target="#2r"/>, could be
             <persName ref="PRS3259CyrilV">Patriarch Cyril V </persName> (in tenure <date>1874–1927</date>).

             The identity of Bishop Sǝrābāmon, mentioned on <locus target="#2r"/>

                    (<foreign xml:lang="gez">ወዲበ፡ ርእሰ፡ ሀገር፡ አበዊነ፡ ብፁእ፡ ጳጳስ፡ አባ፡ ስራባሞን</foreign>)
            is uncertain. He could be Yoḥannā al-ʾAsnāwī, a head of Dayr as-Suryān
            who was consecrated as the bishop of the Sudan with the name
            Ṣarābāmūn in 1897. A later dating to the time of <persName ref="PRS3260CyrilVI">Patriarch Cyril VI</persName>,
          in tenure <time>1959-71</time>, cannot be excluded.</origin>
               </history>

